caption: From the second we walked into the door and greeted by John, I knew I was going to love this place. The fact that he personally knows and remembers his customers is amazing. He remembers the same details to the orders of his customers. The service that was provided was outstanding and the food,  WOW, it was truly amazing. There isn't one complaint that could be said about the food at this restaurant.  It is truly amazing and very authentic. To drive 35 miles to come to this restaurant speaks volumes. If you haven't tried this restaurant,  you can't imagine what you're missing. I will make it a point to visit this restaurant at least once a month if not more. The food has truly made a lasting impression on me.
Consistently good food! Family and I have been going there 20+ yrs.
This spot gives first-rate service and yummy food. My favourite place around town. The food came out rapidly and the prices were economical. Recommended.
Enjoyed every meal I have had at Vicino.

First time trying Vicino and I loved it. I had the shrimp over sauteed spinach and the white pizza. Both were delicious. The white pizza is a favorite of mine. Try Vicino, you will not be disappointed.
Extremely well prepared food.
First-rate environment and super attentive service. The food was crisp and yummy. Will absolutely recommend this place to friends and family. Affordable prices and big meals. Great job.
Wonderful italian restaurant. Great ambiance and food.
Good food best service

The only one Authentic Italian restaurant around in downtown silver spring I have ever been . The food tastes amazing, the price is very reasonable. I wonder why this place been here for over 20 years in downtown silver spring when a lots of business running out business and leave this is the only restaurant pretty much survived . It’s the best experience We have had with my girlfriend .
The best appetizers and the staff are always so friendly and make you feel like family. Stay safe!
Lovely staff!

Walked in and got hit right smack in the face with fresh bread just out of the oven.  Manager full of life and hugs.   Food extreme comfort style food and the desert was worth the arm weasel.  Oh yeah the place is small but soon wonderful.   Thank you.
Horrible, super slow to make the food.
Pizza had potential but was soggy underneath. Crust on the outside was burnt and the cheese was heavy on one side and non existent on the other.
The best Italian restaurant ever..

We came to this place for lunch. This spot was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, we were not disappointed. The staff members welcomed us with a smile and we felt excellent. The food was just great. We enjoyed every moment and we shall absolutely come back again. Keep it up.

We came to this place for dinner. This place was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, it was a winning. The staff were very polite and we had a great feeling. The meal was tasty. We loved this place a lot and we shall definitely come back again. Keep it up.
A favorite in our lives for over 25 years. Warm polite staff and great food. White pizza with fontina is a must appetizer. Whole fish is to die for.
The meals and service were ahead of our expectations. I really liked the vibes of this spot. Awesome place to take the family out for lunch.
The very best Italian- no frills just good food!
Great Food, esp. Fish dishes; good service and homey touches
Fantastic neighborhood restaurant; great food, great prices, and amazing service  ❤️
Good pizza at an excellent price. They seemed also quite generous with add on toppings.

Pastas, salads and house wines are my favorites at Vicino’s. They serve everyone complimentary white pizza squares to start. Everything is cooked to order and does not disappoint. Warm friendly service always. Delicious cappuccino.
Cozy, Great food for  Great Price
Wonderful staff and absolutely delicious white pizza like no other! The desserts are amazing!!
This is a special and charming place! Not fancy, just wonderful.

Excellent food, reasonable prices, somewhat slow service, but most likely due to staffing issues. The waiter was very kind. Delicious home style Italian food.
I've been going to this restaurant for at least a decade. It's always consistently great. My family and I love it.
Arrived today, Christmas Day, to visit family and we were looking for a place that was open to have dinner. What a find! Delicious all around.
Love the food the way everything is organized and how attentive the staff is!!!!! Recommended above and beyond

This is a wonderful restaurant. The staff definitely deliver on that authentic Italian recipe, attention to detail and charm. Every dish I have tried at Vicino's has been a epicurious journey for my tongue. Thank you guys for not veering from tradition
It's a gem. Don't be in a hurry. Enjoy the food. The friendly  people who made it and serve it. The laid back atmosphere. The anachronism of it all in all it's non-snobbish glory.
Always good, well priced and plentiful. We have been coming for years.

nice restaurant, very good food. nice team and good service. I recommend this place if you like Italian food.

great food. great service

This is a very welcoming place that offers a variety of good Italian food.  To start we ordered fried zucchini and fried artichoke hearts, both of which were excellent. I also enjoyed the veal piccata, and the other entrees looked just as good.  The service was attentive.
My "neighborhood favorite" even though I'm not in the neighborhood anymore. Affordable, great food, fantastic service.
Great food with subpar decor. Might see the mayor of DC frequenting here!

First time at this lovely restaurant. Food was excellent. Will return.
Exceptional service and great Italian food. We had a wonderful experience!
Amazing restaurant, and service.

The ambience of this place is to die for. John the owner is extremely polite and friendly. The food is sumptuous and delicious. I recommend everything on the menu, pasta,pizza,subs, seafood...you name it, it's done to perfection. You have to visit this establishment of you visit or live close to downtown silver spring. 10 stars if it were available!!!
Very friendly owner, VERY generous portions of, sadly, overcooked pasta.
Food was good, but service was so-so. Food took a long time despite there not being many people. They forgot my drink as well as my aunt's.
Wish I could give this restaurant more than five stars. The prices are great and the food is even better

Vicino is a diamond in the rough. The restaurant itself looks sketchy when you first walk in but the food is amazing! Every item I've tried has been well cooked and tasty! The wait staff are kind and attentive with the owner usually stopping by each table to say hello and see how you are. At the end of each meal they give you a free tiny portion of icecream that really puts a cherry on top of the whole experience.
I ordered delivery. They didn't provide utensils, napkins, or butter for the bread. Our food was not seasoned. I won't be ordering here again.

As an Italian American, I have one question:  WHY DON'T YOU SEASON YOUR FOOD?  I will never come here again. Two dishes cooked with no spices is two too many.  Edited to say that we had the eggplant parmesan and shrimp alfredo. I am not exaggerating when I say there was no seasoning. None. The marinara and alfredo were very dissatisfying. Plus, it looked like my eggplant was battered then fried, which is unusual. It should be breaded... and seasoned!! Honestly, these are two very simple dishes. I'm embarrassed that this place exists.
I was there for an alumni meeting.  The space downstairs was private and perfect for our session.  The food was freshly prepared and very tasty
Really quaint spot that I might visit again. For a Friday night, it certainly wasn't too busy. To our pleasant surprise, the food was cooked and prepared deliciously!
Food is nice
This place is fantastic! The food is amazing, the staff is warm and friendly, and the ambiance is refreshingly unpretentious and homey. I felt like I was sitting in my grandmother's dining room.
Wait staff was great. Large tasty portions, well priced!
If you haven't been their you need to try it the best Italian pizza white cheese thin crust garlic pizza around and the grilled chicken salad very tasty you will be througly pleased I was!!.
Unfortunate dinner experience.  The chicken parmesan was incredibly tough and the desert was disappointing.

Lovely dining experience a little taste of Italy channeled in downtown Silver Spring.  Food and service was on par! The evening was capped with authentic Italian ice cream...  The ambiance was incredible.  Stop in soon and share the experience.
Very good food, lots of it, very reasonably priced.

I've gone there for years. It is a simple, no frills dining option that is very affordable with a friendly staff. Good Italian comfort food. Basic pasta, good salad, and good garlic bread. I typically enjoy the spaghetti  and veal dishes. Had the eggplant parmigiana for the first time and enjoyed it. The complimentary small serving of ice cream is a nice gesture.

Jason was my server and he is excellent. Very casual and family friendly atmosphere. Not much parking, though. I had the meatballs, which were phenomenal.
Excellent service and food was great. Got treated with multiple freebies. Only comment would be to get rid of the plastic table covers, but other than that, keep up the good work!

We love the restaurant and have been going there for over 20 years.  The food is outstanding,  wonderful staff and the atmosphere from both the staff and patrons is one of pure enjoyment.   We plan to have dinner there tonight.

Excellent Italian food, good service at very reasonable prices.  Outstanding value.  The owner and the staff treat you like family.  The place is nothing fancy; small but intimate.  I would highly recommend it.

Worst food in downtown Silver Spring area. Chair, tablecloths and menus were greasy and dirty. All the food items were topped with huge amount of olive oil and uncooked garlic. Fabulous food. Very decent prices. Best white pizza in history. Service is slow but the people can't be beat - always remember you.

Best little Italian place in all the DMV!! Located right in Silver Spring, can be hard to find for some, but sooo  well worth the hunt. The food is very reasonable priced, especially for the quality. Friendly, courteous staff with the most charming owner I've had the pleasure of dining with. Always generous and delicious! A quaint restaurant with quality food and service. We've been coming here as a family for years and never have had a bad experience. Food is wonderful and fresh!
Refreshingly straightforward; Vicino's food tasted like somebody in the kitchen actually, you know, cooked it. Staff was very friendly and welcoming, prices good. Will visit again.
awesome food.  slow service, but worth the wait

the food is delicious and home cooked to perfection, the owner and wait staff remember you and are so friendly. the Chicken Franchese is to die for and the lasagna. if it's a good day the owner will give extra little appitizers to make you feel at home as well, also super delcious.

I would have rated it one more star, but on two factors it received a dislike two star rating.  First off I ordered on line with Eat24 and said I would like it a 12:25 and I arrived there at 12:22 and it seemed like they did not make it until I arrived and took 20 min to finish my order.  Then I arrived home and opened the box and I found a little surprise in the box a cockroach. yuck!  So I don't think I will be back anytime soon.
Excellent service. Very nice staff. Very good food and prices.

I will not be returning to Vicino's.  I attended a jazz Monday to hear my cousin sing with the jazz group.  They charged each of the four of us a $20 cover INCLUDING the person who was singing.  There was an audience of 8, including our table.  The group was amateur, and didn't merit a cover charge of any kind.  I am a professional musician and have no issues supporting young musicians, but these were teens, not well-known performers.  The menus were not clean, and the food was average at best.  The service was slow despite the small number of diners, and our plates were not cleared, nor our water refilled.  We had to ask the floor manager for both of these things to be done.  After all was said and done, I would have spent the same amount of money on U Street at a club with a headliner and much better cuisine.  This restaurant is scamming customers with their advertisements of jazz nights, and ripping off customers every week.  If you find yourself in the neighborhood go next door or across the street, where you will get value for your money.

The food here is totally delicious and made from fresh ingredients always. Try the Insalata Caprese, the garlic bread, and my favorite: Veal Pizzaiola. The prices are more than reasonable and the service is excellent. Have been going here for many years.

The atmosphere doesn't offer much (plastic covers over the table clothes, etc.).  The prices are very reasonable.  Careful if you are not a garlic fan--it is used liberally in for example, the pasta e fagiole.  overall the food was pretty good.
By far my favorite Italian restaurant in Silver Spring.  The white pizza is to die for.
